My name is Darren, and I&rsquo;m Catholic.
“COG” is short for “Church of God.” It&rsquo;s an umbrella term for all the churches that trace their tradition directly to Herbert W. Armstrong, whose ministry began around 1934 and ended at his death in 1986. He founded the Worldwide Church of God (WCG). The church&rsquo;s splinter groups include&hellip;
Christian Biblical Church of God (CBCG) Church of God - A Worldwide Association (COGWA) Church of God International (CGI) Intercontinental Church of God (ICG) Living Church of God (LCG) Philadelphia Church of God (PCG) Restored Church of God (RCG) United Church of God (UCG) and many others.
